Hi Ken,

No problem. Yes the issues are specific to V2 since the areas of code
were totally re-written as part of V2.

You can fairly easily see the changes in the commit history on github.
Or another nice tool I use is BeyondCompare - great for comparing
files and files within folders; that's what I used to determine that
the UnityNEAT project was very close to the latest code on my github
repository.

   https://github.com/colgreen/sharpneat
   http://www.scootersoftware.com/

Cheers,

Colin
